<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Learn-Software.com – Dependency</title><link>http://localhost:1313/tags/dependency/</link><description>Recent content in Dependency on Learn-Software.com</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 12 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="http://localhost:1313/tags/dependency/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Dependency</title><link>http://localhost:1313/programming/oop/class-relations/dependency/</link><pubDate>Sat, 12 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>http://localhost:1313/programming/oop/class-relations/dependency/</guid><description>
&lt;img src="http://localhost:1313/programming/oop/class-relations/dependency/featured.en_hu_aba78a5178763ba5.jpg" width="640" height="426"/>&lt;p&gt;Key characteristics of dependency:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It represents a &amp;ldquo;uses&amp;rdquo; relationship between classes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s a weaker relationship compared to association, aggregation, or composition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Changes in the used class may affect the using class.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s an example to illustrate dependency:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Printer&lt;/span&gt;:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;print_document&lt;/span&gt;(self, document):
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Printing: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;document&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;get_content()&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;PDFDocument&lt;/span&gt;:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;get_content&lt;/span&gt;(self):
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;PDF content&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;WordDocument&lt;/span&gt;:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;get_content&lt;/span&gt;(self):
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Word document content&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Using the Printer&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;printer &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; Printer()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pdf &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; PDFDocument()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;word &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; WordDocument()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;print(printer&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;print_document(pdf)) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Output: Printing: PDF content&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;print(printer&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;print_document(word)) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Output: Printing: Word document content&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:opacity-0 hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this example, the &lt;code&gt;Printer&lt;/code&gt; class has a dependency on both &lt;code&gt;PDFDocument&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;WordDocument&lt;/code&gt; classes. The &lt;code&gt;Printer&lt;/code&gt; uses these classes in its &lt;code&gt;print_document&lt;/code&gt; method, but it doesn&amp;rsquo;t maintain a long-term relationship with them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s a UML diagram representing these dependency relationships:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div role="img" aria-label="Diagram"&gt;
&lt;pre class="mermaid hx:mt-6"&gt;
classDiagram
class Printer {
+print_document(document)
}
class PDFDocument {
+get_content()
}
class WordDocument {
+get_content()
}
Printer ..&amp;gt; PDFDocument : uses
Printer ..&amp;gt; WordDocument : uses
end
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this diagram, the dashed arrows pointing from &lt;code&gt;Printer&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;PDFDocument&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;WordDocument&lt;/code&gt; indicate dependency. This shows that &lt;code&gt;Printer&lt;/code&gt; uses these classes, but doesn&amp;rsquo;t have a stronger relationship with them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dependency is often used to reduce coupling between classes. By depending on abstractions (like interfaces) rather than concrete classes, we can make our code more flexible and easier to change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-green-200 hx:bg-green-100 hx:text-green-900 hx:dark:border-green-200/30 hx:dark:bg-green-900/30 hx:dark:text-green-200"&gt;
